---
import MainLayout from '../layouts/MainLayout.astro';
---

<MainLayout
  title="Terms of Service - Text Tools Hub"
  description="Review the terms of service governing your use of the Text Tools Hub local web suite."
>
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto flex flex-col gap-6">
    <div class="flex flex-col gap-2">
      <span class="bg-surfaceStrong text-ink text-[11px] font-semibold tracking-[0.08em] uppercase px-2.5 py-1 rounded-full w-fit">
        Compliance
      </span>
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-ink mt-2 mb-3 leading-tight font-display">
        Terms of Service
      </h1>
      <p class="text-[11px] text-muted font-mono">Last updated: July 12, 2026</p>
    </div>

    <div class="prose prose-stone text-xs text-body flex flex-col gap-4 leading-relaxed">
      <p class="text-sm text-body leading-relaxed">
        Welcome to Text Tools Hub. By accessing or using our website, you agree to comply with and be bound by the following terms and conditions. If you do not agree to these terms, please do not use our services.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink mt-4 font-display tracking-tight">1. Use of the Site</h2>
      <p>
        Text Tools Hub provides browser-based text processing utilities. All tool logic is executed locally on your device. You are permitted to use these tools for personal, academic, or commercial purposes.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink mt-4 font-display tracking-tight">2. Proprietary Rights</h2>
      <p>
        The design tokens, codebase layouts, graphical elements, and brand content of Text Tools Hub are our intellectual property and are protected by applicable trademark, copyright, and patent laws. You may not scrape, clone, or republish the tools in bulk without explicit written consent.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink mt-4 font-display tracking-tight">3. Disclaimer of Warranties</h2>
      <p>
        The services on Text Tools Hub are provided on an "as is" and "as available" basis. We make no express or implied warranties that the utilities will run error-free, solve specific developer compiler tasks, or fit every writing check requirement. We assume no liability for the accuracy of formatting or count results.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink mt-4 font-display tracking-tight">4. Limitations of Liability</h2>
      <p>
        In no event shall Text Tools Hub, its contributors, or its operators be held liable for any damages (including, without limitation, damages for loss of data or profit, or due to business interruption) arising out of the use or inability to use the tools, even if notified of the possibility of such damage.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink mt-4 font-display tracking-tight">5. Revisions and Errors</h2>
      <p>
        The materials appearing on Text Tools Hub could include technical, typographical, or photographic errors. We may make changes to the tools, layouts, and legal pages at any time without notice.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink mt-4 font-display tracking-tight">6. Links and Injections</h2>
      <p>
        We do not review all third-party sites linked to our pages and are not responsible for the contents of any such linked site. The inclusion of any link does not imply endorsement by Text Tools Hub.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</MainLayout>
